\par 
\par \hich\af319\dbch\af31505\loch\f319   The hull of the submarine was lashed to the huge pilings, a behemoth
\par \hich\af319\dbch\af31505\loch\f319   strapped in silhouette, the sweeping lines of its bow arcing into the light
\par \hich\af319\dbch\af31505\loch\f319   of the North Sea dawn.
\par \hich\af319\dbch\af31505\loch\f319   The base was on the island of Scharh5rn, in th\hich\af319\dbch\af31505\loch\f319 e Helgoland Bight, several
\par \hich\af319\dbch\af31505\loch\f319   miles from the German mainland and the mouth of the Elbe River. It was a
\par \hich\af319\dbch\af31505\loch\f319   refueling station never detected by Allied Intelligence and, in the cause
\par \hich\af319\dbch\af31505\loch\f319   of security, little known among the strategists of the German High Comniand
\par \hich\af319\dbch\af31505\loch\f319   itself. The undersea marauders came and went in darkness, emerging and
\par \hich\af319\dbch\af31505\loch\f319   submerging within several hundred feet of the moorings. They were Neptunes
\par \hich\af319\dbch\af31505\loch\f319   assassins, come home to rest or going forth to press their attacks.
\par \hich\af319\dbch\af31505\loch\f319   On this particular dawn, however, \hich\af319\dbch\af31505\loch\f319 the submarine lashed to the dock was
\par \hich\af319\dbch\af31505\loch\f319   doing neither. For it, the war was over, its assignment intrinsic to the
\par \hich\af319\dbch\af31505\loch\f319   origins of another war.
\par \hich\af319\dbch\af31505\loch\f319   Two men stood in the well of the conning tower, one in the uniform of a
\par \hich\af319\dbch\af31505\loch\f319   commanding officer of the German Navy, the\hich\af319\dbch\af31505\loch\f319  other a tall civilian in a long
\par \hich\af319\dbch\af31505\loch\f319   dark overcoat-the collar turned up to ward off the North Sea winds--yet
\par \hich\af319\dbch\af31505\loch\f319   hatless, as if to defy the North Sea winter. Both looked down at the long
\par \hich\af319\dbch\af31505\loch\f319   line of passengers who slowly made their way toward the gangplank
\par \hich\af319\dbch\af31505\loch\f319   ami\hich\af319\dbch\af31505\loch\f319 dships. As each passenger reached the plank, a name was checked off
\par \hich\af319\dbch\af31505\loch\f319   against a list, and then he or she was led--or carried -aboard a submarine.
\par \hich\af319\dbch\af31505\loch\f319   A few walked by themselves, but they were the exceptions. They were the
\par \hich\af319\dbch\af31505\loch\f319   oldest, some having reached their \hich\af319\dbch\af31505\loch\f319 twelfth or thirteenth birthdays.
\par \hich\af319\dbch\af31505\loch\f319   The rest were children. Infants in the arms of sternfaced army nurses, who
\par \hich\af319\dbch\af31505\loch\f319   surrendered their charges to a
